{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"bowl, large plate, plastic wrap, refrigerator","id":"r154136","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-wCnywRZgXZ0\/XZQIIkaO3kI\/AAAAAAAAcPo\/lGqK60cKLDoawQE5HiUjT28CajIn-TX7QCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_xuGeQD1USJfy55lP.png","title":"Lentil and mint salad","publishedAt":"2017-09-17T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Ingredients"},{"content":"60 g extra virgin olive oil"},{"content":"30 g lemon juice"},{"content":"1 pinch ground white pepper"},{"content":"½ tsp sea salt, plus an extra 3 pinches"},{"content":"1200 g water"},{"content":"200 g split black lentils"},{"content":"200 g cherry tomatoes, cut into quarters"},{"content":"80 g red onion, cut into thin slices (1-2 mm - see Tips)"},{"content":"2 - 3 sprigs fresh mint, leaves only"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"12.8 g","fat":"16.1 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"26.6 g","calories":"1345 kJ \/ 320 kcal"},"preparations":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Preparation"},{"content":"Place oil, lemon juice, pepper and 3 pinches of the salt into mixing bowl and blend <b>20 sec\/speed 4<b>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside. Do not clean mixing bowl."},{"content":"Place water and remaining ½ teaspoon salt into mixing bowl. Insert simmering basket, weigh lentils into it and cook <b>35 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>. Check to see if lentils are cooked. If necessary, cook for a further <b>5 min\/speed 1<b> or until lentils are cooked to your liking."},{"content":"Remove simmering basket with aid of spatula. Spread lentils onto a plate and set aside to cool to room temperature (approx. 20 minutes)."},{"content":"Place a bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh tomatoes and onion in to it.  Add mint and cooled lentils to the bowl and stir well to combine. Cover with plastic wrap and place into refrigerator for 2-3 hours to allow flavours to develop."},{"content":"Toss with olive oil dressing just before serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Place onion into a bowl of cold water with a pinch of salt to blanch for 10 minutes, then drain and set aside until ready to use (this will help reduce the intensity of the onion).","This salad can be prepared the day before, simply dress just before serving.","Add 2-3 sprigs of coriander leaves just before serving to add even more flavour."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","3h 55m","4 portions"]}